00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:13.000
 Set up your personal and professional email account quickly and efficiently on your Samsung Galaxy S 4 mini. Watch this video to learn how. 

00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:18.000
 Start by touching Apps from a Home screen. Then touch Email. 

00:00:18.000 --> 00:00:24.000
 Enter your email address and password. Touch Next. 

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:30.000
 When the configuration is complete, select the account options such as the email synchronization frequency and tap Next. 

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:33.000
 You have the option to name this account on your phone. 

00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:37.000
 Enter a name if you wish. 

00:00:37.000 --> 00:00:45.000
 Finally, enter your name to display in the sent messages. 

00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:48.000
 Tap OK to go to your email. 

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:53.000
 If you want to add a Microsoft Exchange account from your work or school, tap the menu button. 

00:00:53.000 --> 00:00:56.000
 Select Settings. 

00:00:56.000 --> 00:01:01.000
 Then tap Add account. Enter your email address and password. 

00:01:01.000 --> 00:01:04.000
 Then make sure to touch Config. manual. 

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:10.000
 Choose the type of account to configure, for example Microsoft Exchange ActiveSync. 

00:01:10.000 --> 00:01:13.000
 Enter the required Domain and Exchange Server names. 

00:01:13.000 --> 00:01:26.000
 Contact your company if you do not know this information. 

00:01:26.000 --> 00:01:27.000
 Touch Next when done. 

00:01:27.000 --> 00:01:35.000
 Read the prompt and tap OK if you agree. A second prompt may be needed for remote security, tap OK to continue. 

00:01:35.000 --> 00:01:44.000
 On the Account Options page, you can change email settings such as high-traffic calendar and synchronization options. When finished touch Next. 

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:53.000
 Some accounts must be able to remotely control some security features on your phone, in order to allow the device administrator, touch Activate. 

00:01:53.000 --> 00:02:01.000
 Finally, you have the option to name the new account on your phone, touch OK to complete the configuration. 

00:02:01.000 --> 00:02:05.000
 To see all your accounts together, tap the account menu icon. 

00:02:05.000 --> 00:02:10.000
 Then select Combined View. 

